# SimHub Dashboard & Overlay Conventions

> **Note:** Glob patterns above are provisional. Update them once the dashboard file format and directory structure are finalized.

## Plugin Tab UI (FR-A-012)

- The main plugin tab is HTML-rendered inside SimHub's desktop shell
- Contains the Master Incident List and Detailed Report View
- Keep HTML/CSS self-contained; avoid external dependencies

## In-Game Overlay (FR-A-013)

- Transparent overlay: status indicator, last 3 incidents, "Mark" button
- Minimize screen real estate; overlay must not obstruct driving view
- Design for readability at a glance (large fonts, high contrast)

## Visual Grading (FR-A-014)

Use consistent color coding for incident fault:

| Verdict | Color | Icon |
|---------|-------|------|
| Opponent At Fault | Red (#E53935 or similar) | Red circle |
| Racing Incident | Yellow (#FDD835 or similar) | Yellow circle |
| Player At Fault | Dark/Skull (#424242 or similar) | Skull icon |

## Property Binding

- Expose all data needed by dashboards as SimHub plugin properties
- Name properties with the `SimSteward.` prefix for namespace clarity
- Ensure property updates are throttled appropriately to avoid UI flicker

## Replay Integration (FR-A-015)

- "Review" button wires to `irsdk_BroadcastReplaySearch` targeting `IncidentTime - 30s`
- Provide visual feedback when replay jump is triggered
